{"questionId":"13466","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Steffi the stray cat often visits Will’s house in search of food. Let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n</math></span> be the discrete random&nbsp;variable “the number of times per day that Steffi visits Will’s house”.</p>\n<p>The random variable <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n</math></span> can be modelled by a Poisson distribution with mean 2.1.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the probability that on a randomly selected day, Steffi does not visit Will’s house.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X \\sim {\\text{Po}}\\left( {2.1} \\right)\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n  <mo>∼</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>Po</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2.1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{P}}\\left( {X = 0} \\right) = 0.122\\left( { = {{\\text{e}}^{ - 2.1}}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>P</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mn>0</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.122</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>e</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>2.1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13466","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ2.H_10a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the probability that on a randomly selected day, Steffi does not visit Will’s house.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.7—Discrete random variables","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.8—Binomial distribution","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.17—Poisson distribution"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}